7:
It was the same back at New Year's,
or the race, or with Piamo, or with
Sohvi or Cipher... The source of these
rampaging golems is always the
same...
11:
"That" Golem Club at Voluntas
Academy has made another
request!
15:
They want us to test out a new type
of golem, hm? I don't expect trouble,
yet I cannot shake the feeling of
uneasiness.
20:
Well, I guess we'll need to meet up
with them first. If there's a problem,
we'll deal with it when we get ther—
32:
Hey there, adventurers! For your own
safety, please step aside for a
moment!
42:
Wahahaha! I'm Dedalia, leader of
the Golem Club at Voluntas
Academy! Watch me go!
54:
Sheesh. Didn't think I'd lose control
again. I wonder what caused it this
time?
58:
Hey, thanks for holding this guy off.
You're not hurt or anything, are y—
62:
Huh?! You're the ones always
stopping my rampaging golems,
aren't you?!
73:
*sigh* We haven't even gotten
started, and I already feel tired...
77:
Wahaha, sorry!
I just want to make sure you know
how thankful I am for you always
stopping those golems.
81:
Also, thanks for accepting my
request today!
86:
That request involving the new
golem was from you, then?
90:
Yup. I want you to test out these new
features I've installed by battling
Tharros-99 here!
94:
Whaddayathink? He's got a
dual-activation core magical
exhaust system! Look at the sparkle
of arcane power surging through his
layered control systems!
98:
Tharros is the very embodiment of
technological innovation once
considered impossible!
102:
You're listening, right? I'm changing
golem history! It's awesome, right?
RIGHT?!
106:
I-it appears to simply be a combat
golem... I don't notice anything too
unusual...
113:
Y-your grasp of theory is incredible!
W-we can't even wrap our minds
around it...
120:
U-um... Anyway, you want me to
fight it, right? Should we start now?
124:
Heh-heh, yes... I'll show you just how
amazing Tharros is, here and now!
129: Now then... Let the test begin!
141:
Wahaha! Indeed! Tharros is a
mighty golem equipped with
nothing but the very bleeding edge
of Shibuyan technology!
144:
This is nothing like your average
malfunctioning labor golem, I
assure you!
161: What the heck kinda sword is that?!
170:
Pardon the intrusion. Dedalia? Your
sponsor has arrived.
175:
Huh? Oh, for the runaway golem
thing, I guess...
177:
I mean, I told you that thing was all
burned out. Pretty sure I warned you
to do proper maintenance...
183:
Dedalia's golems are so brilliant that
demand for them never runs out,
but this also means that they're
made with all sorts of special
considerations in mind.
185:
That's why if you treat them a little
roughly, they might start to
malfunction...
189:
Does that mean... All of the previous
incidents with golems weren't
caused by problems with the
golems themselves?
193:
Oh, no. Dedalia is regularly at fault.
Her reckless design choices are very
often the cause of the rampaging
golems.
196:
B-but still, I don’t mean to say that
it's always her fault every time.
199:
...I see. I suppose we were somewhat
mistaken.
202:
P-please! We need you to prepare
another golem for us as soon as
possible! We'll go out of business
without your help!
205:
No.
Nobody understands my theories...
And I lost to Alk.
207:
Being a genius is so lonely...
I'm so... demotivated...
210:
Please, someone! I'll pay you, just
get her to help me!
213:
W-we don't know what to do about
this, either...
233:
You BET! I feel like I could come up
with every idea in the universe right
now! Wahahaha!
238:
Good. In that case, helping out your
sponsor shouldn't be a problem—
242: I don't want to do that, though.
251:
I feel amazing right now, after all!
I've got so many ideas I need to
execute right now! NOW!
255:
U-uh... How about this, then? If you
make something for your sponsor,
then we'll bring you here again!
263:
Ah! While I'm at it, I'll try creating that
multi-element core I just thought of!
266:
No, wait... You can't make the thing
too difficult to maintain...
270: Right, right. Just leave it to me!
274:
Nothing's too difficult for Dida the
super genius! Wahahaha!
